<HEAD>Mrs. Thatcher's Daughter Briefly Held By Customs</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Retransmitting to fix garble.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Customs agents at Heathrow Airport detained the
daughter of Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher and took an expensive
watch from her because there was no proof it was not an illegal
import, The Mail on Sunday reported.
   The weekly said Carol Thatcher, 35, was questioned for 15 minutes
about the watch when she returned Nov. 27 from an assignment in
Pakistan.
   The watch was valued at $2,760 and when she reclaimed it several
days later she had to pay $185 import duty and a tax of $27, the
report said.
   An unidentified spokesman for Miss Thatcher was quoted as saying:
``She was given the watch in this country and has worn it while
coming in and out of Britain on several occasions.''
