<HEAD>Explosion Sets Off Fire in Market Area; 15 Reported Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion set off a fire in a major market
Sunday, apparently in fireworks stands set up for the holidays, and
initial reports said at least 15 people were injured, the Red Cross
and fire department said.
   ``Powder in the fireworks exploded and the fire extended to a
building,'' said Vicente Renero, on duty at the fire department.
``It appears there are quite a few injured.''
   He said the fire in the Merced market was reported at 2:40 p.m.
   Jose Pinajero of the Red Cross said 15 people suffered burns but
none of them seriously enough to endanger their lives.
   He said a series of explosions were believed to have occurred in
the fireworks stands, but the report was not yet confirmed.
   For years, the Merced was the main market in this city of 18
million, supplying dozens of other markets and individual customers.
A a new main market was built on the edge of the city, but the
Merced remains important because of tradition and its more
convenient location.
   Fireworks merchants set up stands in the area for holidays, such
as Independence Day in September and Christmas and New Year's.
