<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Opens Strong; Tokyo Shares Slightly Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar advanced in early trading Monday
against the Japanese yen, while prices on the Tokyo Stock Exchange
rose slightly.
   The dollar opened at 122.70 yen, up 0.27 yen from Friday's close
of 122.43 yen.
   Traders said the dollar's rise followed its strength on the
Sydney market, which opened earlier than Tokyo.
   A dealer at a major commercial bank said the dollar was expected
to trade in a narrow range until Wednesday, when the U.S. Commerce
Department is scheduled to release the nation's trade figures for
October.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei stock average of 225
selected issues, a 34.52-point winner Friday, rose 40.35 points, or
0.13 percent, to advance to 29,833.77 shortly after the market
opened.
</TEXT>
